textBeforeTable: The United Kennel Club is very pleased with the final count of 737 coonhounds, representing 35 US states and Canada, that pre-entered the 53rd Annual Autumn Oaks Nite Hunt. Many of their owners, who make this event a part of their annual vacation, will already be making their way towards Richmond, Indiana early next week. Although the Autumn Oaks hunt will not kick off until Friday, there's lots of other activities including the Black Gold 2000 Slam Series available to them leading up to the Labor Day weekend. On Tuesday, the Hanna's Creek Conservation Club in Liberty will host the first of this three night Slam Series. Black Gold Dog Food provides added purses of $500, in addition to regular payouts, for each of the three events. They also provide an additional $500 to the owner of the dog who accumulates the most cast wins at the three events.
